\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\color black
The desired regions to extract are the bright and shaded areas.
 The threshold values for these can be determined from the image's mean
 and standard deviation intensity values:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\color black
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
T_{high}=\mu_{i}+\rho_{high}\cdot\sigma_{i}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\color black
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
